23rd Nov 2014 BBC2 HD
2:45pm to 5pm Live

Jacqui Oatley presents from Wembley as England take on Germany in a women's international. The England team have been on a fantastic run under Mark Sampson, qualifying for 2015's World Cup in Canada with a 100 per cent record from their group. They will face the sternest of tests against Germany, who have lifted the European Championship crown on six successive occasions, but will have a record crowd for an England women's match to cheer them on.
